Our Reporter  Football fans will be treated to a bumper package this weekend as games from the English Premier League will be aired on GOtv this weekend. The games, scheduled to hold from March 14 to 15, will be broadcast live on SuperSport Select 2 to GOtv Jolli and GOtv Max subscribers. A fascinating game lies in prospect as Manchester City host Burnley at the Etihad Stadium. The game kicks off at 4pm and will be aired live on SuperSport Select 2. Manchester City are now hoping to cement their second position on the log and Coach Pep Guardiola will be hoping that the team can bounce back from their recent difficulties and finish the season on a high.  Burnley, on the other hand, may not have hit the heights of their performance three seasons ago but they are having a decent season, currently placed in 10th position. Also tomorrow, Chelsea will want to cement their fourth place when they visit Aston Villa at Villa Park. The game will be aired live on SuperSport Select 4 at 6:30pm.  Aston Villa battling to escape relegation, as they are rooted in the 19th position having lost four consecutive games and managed a solitary win in their last five matches. Chelsea, however, are glittering in the top half of the table after claiming a vital win against Everton last week. The Blues are in prime position to pick the fourth and final spot for next seasonâ€™s UEFA Champions League.